text:
You remember the little song? And so, I was going along humming that little song. I thought, Now, I just about got it. I thought,
They were gathered in the upper room,
All praying in His name;
They were baptized with the Holy Ghost,
And power for service came;
What He did for them that day,
He'll do for you the same;
I'm so glad that I can say I'm one of them.
I had my letters in my hand, and I was just a stepping down the street. I started across the street, and when I did, Something said, "Stop." I start … "Stop." It was Him. I thought, Well…
[Blank spot on tape]… and I walked and I walked. I was going to ask somebody where the post office was. And I just kept walking, walked right on by the hotel. I just kept walking. I didn't know where I was going; just kept on walking, walking, walking, walking.

text_no:
Husker du den lille sangen? Så, jeg gikk langs og nynnet på den lille sangen. Jeg tenkte, Nå har jeg den nesten. Jeg tenkte,
De var samlet i øvre rom,
Alle ba i Hans navn;
De ble døpt med Den Hellige Ånd,
Og kraft til tjeneste kom;
Det Han gjorde for dem den dagen,
Vil Han gjøre for deg også;
Jeg er så glad for at jeg kan si jeg er en av dem.
Jeg hadde brevene i hånden og gikk nedover gaten. Jeg begynte å krysse gaten, og da jeg gjorde det, sa noe, "Stopp." Jeg begynte å … "Stopp." Det var Ham. Jeg tenkte, Vel…
[Tomt.område.på.lydbånd]… og jeg gikk og gikk. Jeg skulle spørre noen hvor postkontoret var. Og jeg bare fortsatte å gå, gikk rett forbi hotellet. Jeg bare fortsatte å gå. Jeg visste ikke hvor jeg skulle; bare fortsatte å gå, gå, gå, gå.
